Software#SystemSoftware#OperatingSystem#.name: CmdList
Software#SystemSoftware#OperatingSystem#.description:
windows command syntax:
	*.exe can be executed using *, but *.cpl should be executed using *.cpl
	win+R maybe case sensive, but CMD is not.
	rem means specification, so there must has a white space after rem
	it's better not use number as the beginning of a variable when declear, otherwise will cause unexception, such as directory path declear
	if the path contains whitespace character, it's better use "path", otherwirse some unexception will occur, because cmd will consider whitespace as command stopping when complier.
	if the path contains "(" or ")" character, it's better use "path", otherwirse some unexception will occur, because cmd will consider "(" or ")" as command stopping when complier.
	continue operator: ^
	Accessing xxx.bat must locate to the directory first, otherwise will failed
	Accessing xxx.exe can use command:start, and need not locate to the directory
	mshta vbscript:msgbox("提示内容",64,"提示框Title")(window.close)
